        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 27 at 10:36AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 1036 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Callaghan, or 8 miles southwest of Encinal, moving southeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Encinal, Las Tiendas, Botines, Ranchitos Las Lomas, and Callaghan.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 35 between mile markers 14 and 40.
US Highway 59 between mile markers 800 and 816.
US Highway 83 between mile markers 680 and 698.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
